{"lemma":"كُورٌ","slug":"كُورٌ","root":"ك.#.ر","root_slug":"ك-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37361"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to roll, to roll up, to coil, to wind"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make round"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to clench"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"camel saddle"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"furnace, smelting furnace, forge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bellows"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of كُرَة (kura, “ball”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of كُورَة (kūra)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"An early Semitic borrowing, ultimately derived from Sumerian 𒄥 (gur, “to twist, to wind, to turn”).\n\nLikely through Aramaic from Akkadian 𒆠𒉈 (/⁠kuru⁠/, “crucible, kiln, brazier; log, thick reed; short reed mat, collection of reeds”), likely coined from Sumerian 𒄥 (gur, “a bundle”), hence a place of burning bundles of firewood or tinder. The sense of a saddle originally stems from a bundle or mat rolled and placed for cushioning; a specified sense natively coined from Akkadian 𒄀𒆤𒈣 (/⁠kuru⁠/, “short reed mat, collection or roll of reeds; a woven thing”), from Sumerian 𒄥 (gur, “to twist, to wind, to turn”).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37361","headword_ar":"كُورٌ","root":"kwr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaworN","text_ar":"كَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A camel's"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saddle of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makowarN","text_ar":"مَكْوَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mukowar~N","text_ar":"مُكْوَرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the latter with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"and teshdeed to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TS, L:] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with its apparatus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) pronounced by many"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaworN","text_ar":"كَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is a mistake: (IAth:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akowaArN","text_ar":"اَكْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akowurN","text_ar":"اَكْوُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and (of mult., TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiyraAnN","text_ar":"كِيرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwraAnN","text_ar":"كُورَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuw^uwrN","text_ar":"كُوُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which last, says ISd, is extr. as a pl. form of a sing. such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kwr","text_ar":"كور"},{"kind":"text","text":"with an infirm letter. (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A blacksmith's fire-place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * A, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majomarap","text_ar":"مَجْمَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constructed of clay:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K: *) and also said to signify the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which he blows his fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb, TA:) or this latter is called [only]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiyrN","text_ar":"كِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, in the present art.; and S, Msb, K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kyr","text_ar":"كير"},{"kind":"text","text":":) an arabicized word. (Msb.)       -A4-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hornets',"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bees', nest;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"structure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hornets:"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~anaAbiyr","text_ar":"الزَّنَابِير"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, K [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~anaAniyr","text_ar":"الدَّنَانِير"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a mistake:]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of bees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(accord. to a trad. cited in the TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akowaArN","text_ar":"اَكْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwaArapN","text_ar":"كُوَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","Msb","IAth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}